author: Marc Weiszer
title: Georgia-Missouri kick time/TV set
text:
UGA backup Hunter Long at the ready again while Brandon Kublanow banged up 
Georgia will have its latest kickoff of the season so far when Missouri comes to town. 
The Oct. 17 game at Sanford Stadium is set for 7:30 p.m. on the SEC Network, the conference announced Monday afternoon. The matchup is Georgia's homecoming game. 
All of Georgiaâ€™s games this season have either kicked at noon or 3:30 p.m. except for the Sept. 19 home game against South Carolina, which was a 6 p.m. start time. 
Georgia, now No. 19 in the AP poll, plays at Tennessee Saturday at 3:30 p.m. on CBS.
